om/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>I really can't believe what happened next, his pet ate mine in under 10 seconds and he was laughing so hard I had to run to the zone before it ate me too.  before pet died it had done about 1 bub of damge to his pet.  This is in no way a whine about us vs mages but i'm left pondering if there's something thats happening in duel that makes putting pet against pet an invalid test,  how can my pet possibly do so well against dragon constructs but last a mere few seconds against a mage pet?  <br><br>Any epic mages who can explain why this might've been the case. I'm very happy with my pets ability to tank and although i'd like some damage upgrade, Its not the fact that it beat my pet thats so bothering its how quickly it done it compared to what a higher level mob would've done.  also, i never slowed his pet as did I not slow the DC.  Could it be possible he slapped on a dam sheild and my pet killed itself? or perhaps epic pet has its own damage shield.   <p></center><center> <a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=225328">Venerable Kryten Smeghead, Level 60 shaman</a></center><center> <a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=276084">Rippler Smeghead, Level 60 Savage Lord</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/uspriteshinslayer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sprite Shinslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beast</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#FF9933>(9/5/02 6:56:27 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.comresinc.com/puck/spongebob.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Fair to compare with mage pets?</span><hr size=1> Yes Mage epic has its own DS <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227031">Gatorg